snippets.title: monitoring listAlertPolicies Sample
snippets.description: Lists the existing alerting policies for the workspace.

snippets.title: monitoring getAlertPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single alerting policy.

snippets.title: monitoring createAlertPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new alerting policy. Design your application to single-thread API calls that modify the state of alerting policies in a single project. This includes calls to CreateAlertPolicy, DeleteAlertPolicy and UpdateAlertPolicy.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteAlertPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Deletes an alerting policy. Design your application to single-thread API calls that modify the state of alerting policies in a single project. This includes calls to CreateAlertPolicy, DeleteAlertPolicy and UpdateAlertPolicy.

snippets.title: monitoring updateAlertPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Updates an alerting policy. You can either replace the entire policy with a new one or replace only certain fields in the current alerting policy by specifying the fields to be updated via `updateMask`. Returns the updated alerting policy. Design your application to single-thread API calls that modify the state of alerting policies in a single project. This includes calls to CreateAlertPolicy, DeleteAlertPolicy and UpdateAlertPolicy.

snippets.title: monitoring listGroups Sample
snippets.description: Lists the existing groups.

snippets.title: monitoring getGroup Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single group.

snippets.title: monitoring createGroup Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new group.

snippets.title: monitoring updateGroup Sample
snippets.description: Updates an existing group. You can change any group attributes except `name`.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteGroup Sample
snippets.description: Deletes an existing group.

snippets.title: monitoring listGroupMembers Sample
snippets.description: Lists the monitored resources that are members of a group.

snippets.title: monitoring listMonitoredResourceDescriptors Sample
snippets.description: Lists monitored resource descriptors that match a filter.

snippets.title: monitoring getMonitoredResourceDescriptor Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single monitored resource descriptor.

snippets.title: monitoring listMetricDescriptors Sample
snippets.description: Lists metric descriptors that match a filter.

snippets.title: monitoring getMetricDescriptor Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single metric descriptor.

snippets.title: monitoring createMetricDescriptor Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new metric descriptor. The creation is executed asynchronously. User-created metric descriptors define [custom metrics](https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/custom-metrics). The metric descriptor is updated if it already exists, except that metric labels are never removed.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteMetricDescriptor Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a metric descriptor. Only user-created [custom metrics](https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/custom-metrics) can be deleted.

snippets.title: monitoring listTimeSeries Sample
snippets.description: Lists time series that match a filter.

snippets.title: monitoring createTimeSeries Sample
snippets.description: Creates or adds data to one or more time series. The response is empty if all time series in the request were written. If any time series could not be written, a corresponding failure message is included in the error response. This method does not support [resource locations constraint of an organization policy](https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/docs/organization-policy/defining-locations#setting_the_organization_policy).

snippets.title: monitoring createServiceTimeSeries Sample
snippets.description: Creates or adds data to one or more service time series. A service time series is a time series for a metric from a Google Cloud service. The response is empty if all time series in the request were written. If any time series could not be written, a corresponding failure message is included in the error response. This endpoint rejects writes to user-defined metrics. This method is only for use by Google Cloud services. Use [projects.timeSeries.create][google.monitoring.v3.MetricService.CreateTimeSeries] instead.

snippets.title: monitoring listNotificationChannelDescriptors Sample
snippets.description: Lists the descriptors for supported channel types. The use of descriptors makes it possible for new channel types to be dynamically added.

snippets.title: monitoring getNotificationChannelDescriptor Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single channel descriptor. The descriptor indicates which fields are expected / permitted for a notification channel of the given type.

snippets.title: monitoring listNotificationChannels Sample
snippets.description: Lists the notification channels that have been created for the project. To list the types of notification channels that are supported, use the `ListNotificationChannelDescriptors` method.

snippets.title: monitoring getNotificationChannel Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single notification channel. The channel includes the relevant configuration details with which the channel was created. However, the response may truncate or omit passwords, API keys, or other private key matter and thus the response may not be 100% identical to the information that was supplied in the call to the create method.

snippets.title: monitoring createNotificationChannel Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new notification channel, representing a single notification endpoint such as an email address, SMS number, or PagerDuty service. Design your application to single-thread API calls that modify the state of notification channels in a single project. This includes calls to CreateNotificationChannel, DeleteNotificationChannel and UpdateNotificationChannel.

snippets.title: monitoring updateNotificationChannel Sample
snippets.description: Updates a notification channel. Fields not specified in the field mask remain unchanged. Design your application to single-thread API calls that modify the state of notification channels in a single project. This includes calls to CreateNotificationChannel, DeleteNotificationChannel and UpdateNotificationChannel.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteNotificationChannel Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a notification channel. Design your application to single-thread API calls that modify the state of notification channels in a single project. This includes calls to CreateNotificationChannel, DeleteNotificationChannel and UpdateNotificationChannel.

snippets.title: monitoring sendNotificationChannelVerificationCode Sample
snippets.description: Causes a verification code to be delivered to the channel. The code can then be supplied in `VerifyNotificationChannel` to verify the channel.

snippets.title: monitoring getNotificationChannelVerificationCode Sample
snippets.description: Requests a verification code for an already verified channel that can then be used in a call to VerifyNotificationChannel() on a different channel with an equivalent identity in the same or in a different project. This makes it possible to copy a channel between projects without requiring manual reverification of the channel. If the channel is not in the verified state, this method will fail (in other words, this may only be used if the SendNotificationChannelVerificationCode and VerifyNotificationChannel paths have already been used to put the given channel into the verified state). There is no guarantee that the verification codes returned by this method will be of a similar structure or form as the ones that are delivered to the channel via SendNotificationChannelVerificationCode; while VerifyNotificationChannel() will recognize both the codes delivered via SendNotificationChannelVerificationCode() and returned from GetNotificationChannelVerificationCode(), it is typically the case that the verification codes delivered via SendNotificationChannelVerificationCode() will be shorter and also have a shorter expiration (e.g. codes such as "G-123456") whereas GetVerificationCode() will typically return a much longer, websafe base 64 encoded string that has a longer expiration time.

snippets.title: monitoring verifyNotificationChannel Sample
snippets.description: Verifies a `NotificationChannel` by proving receipt of the code delivered to the channel as a result of calling `SendNotificationChannelVerificationCode`.

snippets.title: monitoring queryTimeSeries Sample
snippets.description: Queries time series by using Monitoring Query Language (MQL). We recommend using PromQL instead of MQL. For more information about the status of MQL, see the [MQL deprecation notice](https://cloud.google.com/stackdriver/docs/deprecations/mql).

snippets.title: monitoring createService Sample
snippets.description: Create a `Service`.

snippets.title: monitoring getService Sample
snippets.description: Get the named `Service`.

snippets.title: monitoring listServices Sample
snippets.description: List `Service`s for this Metrics Scope.

snippets.title: monitoring updateService Sample
snippets.description: Update this `Service`.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteService Sample
snippets.description: Soft delete this `Service`.

snippets.title: monitoring createServiceLevelObjective Sample
snippets.description: Create a `ServiceLevelObjective` for the given `Service`.

snippets.title: monitoring getServiceLevelObjective Sample
snippets.description: Get a `ServiceLevelObjective` by name.

snippets.title: monitoring listServiceLevelObjectives Sample
snippets.description: List the `ServiceLevelObjective`s for the given `Service`.

snippets.title: monitoring updateServiceLevelObjective Sample
snippets.description: Update the given `ServiceLevelObjective`.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteServiceLevelObjective Sample
snippets.description: Delete the given `ServiceLevelObjective`.

snippets.title: monitoring createSnooze Sample
snippets.description: Creates a `Snooze` that will prevent alerts, which match the provided criteria, from being opened. The `Snooze` applies for a specific time interval.

snippets.title: monitoring listSnoozes Sample
snippets.description: Lists the `Snooze`s associated with a project. Can optionally pass in `filter`, which specifies predicates to match `Snooze`s.

snippets.title: monitoring getSnooze Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `Snooze` by `name`.

snippets.title: monitoring updateSnooze Sample
snippets.description: Updates a `Snooze`, identified by its `name`, with the parameters in the given `Snooze` object.

snippets.title: monitoring listUptimeCheckConfigs Sample
snippets.description: Lists the existing valid Uptime check configurations for the project (leaving out any invalid configurations).

snippets.title: monitoring getUptimeCheckConfig Sample
snippets.description: Gets a single Uptime check configuration.

snippets.title: monitoring createUptimeCheckConfig Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new Uptime check configuration.

snippets.title: monitoring updateUptimeCheckConfig Sample
snippets.description: Updates an Uptime check configuration. You can either replace the entire configuration with a new one or replace only certain fields in the current configuration by specifying the fields to be updated via `updateMask`. Returns the updated configuration.

snippets.title: monitoring deleteUptimeCheckConfig Sample
snippets.description: Deletes an Uptime check configuration. Note that this method will fail if the Uptime check configuration is referenced by an alert policy or other dependent configs that would be rendered invalid by the deletion.

snippets.title: monitoring listUptimeCheckIps Sample
snippets.description: Returns the list of IP addresses that checkers run from.
